choices.text: the 2018 general elections. The elections were held on 25 July 2018, and the results were announced on 26 July 2018. The Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf (PTI) won the elections and formed the government. The PTI won 116 seats in the National Assembly, while the Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N) won 64 seats. The Pakistan Peoples Party (PPP) won 43 seats. The Pakistan Muslim League-Quaid (PML-Q) won 11 seats. The Muttahida Majlis-e-Amal (MMA) won 11 seats. The Balochistan Awami Party (BAP) won 8 seats. The Awami National Party (ANP) won 7 seats. The Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam-Fazl (JUI-F) won 6 seats. The Pakistan Muslim League-Functional (PML-F) won 5 seats. The Pakistan Muslim League-Quaid-e-Azam (PML-QA) won 4 seats. The Pakistan Muslim League-Functional (PML-F) won 4 seats. The Pakistan Muslim League-Functional (PML-F) won 4 seats.
